HEADWORD: Flavaniline
<hw>Fla*van"i*line</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?; 104)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>flavus</ets> yellow + E. <ets>aniline</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A yellow, crystalline, organic dyestuff,
<chform>C16H14N2</chform>, of artificial production. It is a strong
base, and is a complex derivative of aniline and quinoline.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flavescent</ent>⟦br⟧
